      <h1 class="h4 mb-3">7. Control in-flight form disabling with <code>het-background</code></h1>
      <div class="tutorial-content mb-4">
        <p>While a request is in flight, HET marks the target pane busy and disables interactive controls in that pane. For forms, HET also disables the submitting form's controls by default.</p>
        <p>Use <code>het-background</code> to keep a form interactive during submission while still marking the target pane busy.</p>
        <p>This is useful for low-risk background updates such as previews or live filters.</p>
        <p>Relevant reference:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="reference/requests#core-attributes">Core attributes</a></li>
          <li><a href="reference/requests#ui-feedback-while-requests-are-in-flight">UI feedback while requests are in flight</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

